    influence: "Fed the North Caucasus: the first automated mill in Europe became a symbol of industrial mercy.",
    impactLong: "Aga Bala Guliyev built a unique enterprise for its time in Stavropol — a fully automated technological mill that surpassed European counterparts. His network of steam mills from Tiflis to Armavir supplied cheap flour and bread to the entire North Caucasus and part of Transcaucasia; during hungry years and in the First World War, Guliyev distributed bread for free, saving tens of thousands of families from starvation. His philanthropy united Muslim and Orthodox communities: with his funds, schools were built where children of different faiths studied, as well as mosques, shelters, and medical centers. The preserved mill and Guliyev's manor house in Stavropol are now federal architectural monuments.",
