    full: "In 1895 the Swedish chemist and inventor of dynamite Alfred Nobel signed a will under which almost his entire fortune — about 31 million Swedish kronor — was transferred to a fund to establish annual prizes for those who brought «the greatest benefit to humanity». The prizes are awarded in physics, chemistry, physiology or medicine, literature and for work to promote peace; in 1968 the prize in economic sciences in memory of Nobel was added. The first prizes were awarded in 1901. Over more than a century the Nobel Prize has become the most authoritative mark of recognition in the world and turned the private fortune of a single industrialist into a perpetual institution of service to humanity.",
